dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 24.100000. South Decimal Degree 24.066667. East Decimal Degree 120.550000. West Decimal Degree 120.516667. Alternate title: Shoka. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:6,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Place names are transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Chang-hua. Compiled from aerial photgraphy dated March 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2219-II, 1944. Formosa 1:50,000, Japanese Imperial and Survey, Taichu, 1928; Shoka, Guide to Taiwan Railroads, 1935. Additional information from intelligence data.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
